{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775818838177,"sessionID":"ses_288f65bbcffe5TdygA1wWgT13C","part":{"id":"prt_d7709ac59001BEkYFnffVpBKr5","messageID":"msg_d7709a538001II1mfXH8k5ub46","sessionID":"ses_288f65bbcffe5TdygA1wWgT13C","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_7be025b756ac4d37969e5e14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure and architecture\n2. The pkg/workloadmanager module - what files exist, what they do, current implementation\n3. Any existing sandbox-related code, lifecycle management patterns\n4. How tasks/checklists are typically structured in this project (look for tasks.md, TODO, or similar files)\n5. Any existing Stage ST-3 completion artifacts or design documents\n6. Testing patterns used in the project\n7. Any related modules or dependencies that interact with workloadmanager\n\nSearch broadly across the project. Look for:\n- pkg/workloadmanager/ directory contents\n- Any sandbox-related code\n- Design docs, architecture docs\n- Existing task lists or checklists\n- Test files for workloadmanager\n- Configuration files related to sandbox/lifecycle\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of what you find, including file paths and key code patterns.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_288f641ffffeIXnIDAhsR5Db0L (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive AgentCube Project Analysis\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure and Architecture\n\n**Project Root:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z`\n\n**Module:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (Go 1.25.0)\n\n**Purpose:** AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents. It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n**Top-Level Directory Structure:**\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── pkg/                          # Go packages\n│   ├── apis/runtime/v1alpha1/    # CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n│   └── workloadmanager/          # HTTP service for sandbox lifecycle management\n│       ├── handler/              # HTTP request handlers\n│       └── response/             # Response helper utilities\n├── client-go/                    # Generated Kubernetes typed client\n│   ├── clientset/                # Versioned clientset\n│   ├── informers/                # Shared informer factory\n│   └── listers/                  # Listers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n├── changes/                      # Change requests (AR-001 through AR-006)\n│   ├── AR-001/                   # AgentRuntime CRD type definition\n│   ├── AR-002/                   # CodeInterpreter CRD type definition\n│   ├── AR-003/                   # Shared types and constants\n│   ├── AR-004/                   # WorkloadManager HTTP service framework\n│   ├── AR-005/                   # Sandbox creation handler\n│   └── AR-006/                   # Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management\n├── sandbox-orchestration/        # Top-level design doc and spec\n├── session-store/                # Redis/Valkey session store design\n├── idle-cleanup/                 # Agentd idle cleanup controller design\n├── session-routing/              # Router design\n├── code-execution/               # PicoD code execution engine design\n├── cli-toolkit/                  # CLI tool design\n├── python-sdk/                   # Python SDK design\n├── deployment/                   # Deployment design\n├── ci-cd/                        # CI/CD design\n├── integrations/                 # Integration design\n├── testing/                      # TDD manifest\n├── design.md                     # AR-003 design doc (at root)\n├── delta-spec.md                 # AR-004 requirement spec (BDD format)\n├── test_spec.md                  # TDD specification\n├── project.md                    # Project context document\n├── go.mod / go.sum               # Go module files\n└── coverage.out                  # Coverage output\n```\n\n**Architecture Diagram (from project.md):**\n\n```\nClient / SDK / CLI\n  -> Router (Deployment :8080)\n     <-> Redis/Valkey (session store)\n     -> WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n        <-> Redis/Valkey\n        -> K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. The `pkg/workloadmanager` Module -- Complete Analysis\n\n**Current Files:**\n\n| File | Path | Lines | Description |\n|------|------|-------|-------------|\n| `sandbox_create.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go` | 687 | **Sandbox creation handler** -- implements `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox` and `CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox` HTTP handlers |\n| `models.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go` | 57 | Request/response DTOs: `CreateSandboxRequest`, `CreateSandboxResponse`, `SandboxInfo`, `SandboxStatus`, `EntryPoint` |\n| `constants.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/constants.go` | 53 | GVR constants, Kind constants, label/annotation keys, default values |\n| `response.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/response/response.go` | 45 | HTTP response helpers: `JSON()`, `Created()`, `Error()`, `ErrorWithID()` |\n| `response_test.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/response/response_test.go` | 108 | Unit tests for response helpers (6 test functions) |\n\n**Key Interfaces Defined in `sandbox_create.go`:**\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, info *SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *SandboxInfo) error\n}\n\ntype SandboxReconcilerWatcher interface {\n    WatchSandboxOnce(namespace, name string) (<-chan SandboxStatus, error)\n}\n\ntype TokenCache interface {\n    GetOrCreateUserK8sClient(namespace, saName, token string) (dynamic.Interface, error)\n}\n\ntype UserClientFactory interface {\n    CreateUserClient(token string) (dynamic.Interface, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Key Constants in `constants.go`:**\n\n```go\n// GVRs\nAgentRuntimeGVR    = {Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\"}\nCodeInterpreterGVR = {Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\"}\nSandboxGVR         = {Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\"}\nSandboxClaimGVR    = {Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\"}\n\n// Defaults\nDefaultSandboxTTL         = 8   // hours\nDefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15  // minutes\n```\n\n**Sandbox Creation Flow (from `sandbox_create.go`):**\n1. Parse and validate `CreateSandboxRequest`\n2. Look up template (AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter) from informer cache\n3. Generate SessionID (UUID v4) and SandboxName (`{workloadName}-{random8}`)\n4. Build Sandbox CR (unstructured) from template\n5. Store placeholder `SandboxInfo` in Store\n6. Register one-shot watcher via `reconciler.WatchSandboxOnce()`\n7. Create CR via dynamic client\n8. Wait up to 2 minutes for \"running\" status (with rollback on timeout)\n9. Resolve Pod IP (3-tier fallback: direct name -> annotation -> label selector)\n10. Build EntryPoints from Pod IP + ports\n11. Update Store with full info, return response\n\n**What is MISSING from workloadmanager (planned in AR-004/AR-006):**\n- `config.go` -- Configuration management\n- `server.go` -- Server lifecycle (Run, Shutdown)\n- `routes.go` -- Route registration\n- `handler/health.go` -- Health check endpoints\n- `handler/agent_runtime.go` -- AgentRuntime CRUD handlers\n- `handler/code_interpreter.go` -- CodeInterpreter CRUD handlers\n- `handler/sandbox_delete.go` -- Sandbox deletion handler (AR-006)\n- `handler/garbage_collector.go` -- Background GC (AR-006)\n- `middleware/request_id.go` -- Request ID middleware\n\n---\n\n### 3. Sandbox-Related Code and Lifecycle Management Patterns\n\n**Sandbox Lifecycle Components:**\n\n| Component | Location | Role |\n|-----------|----------|------|\n| **Sandbox Creation** | `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go` | Creates Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs from templates |\n| **Sandbox Deletion** | `changes/AR-006/design.md` (planned) | DELETE endpoints + Store cleanup |\n| **Garbage Collector** | `changes/AR-006/design.md` (planned) | 15s tick, cleanup expired/inactive sandboxes |\n| **Idle Cleanup** | `idle-cleanup/design.md` | Agentd reconciler deletes sandboxes after idle timeout |\n| **Session Store** | `session-store/design.md` | Redis/Valkey persistence of SandboxInfo |\n\n**Sandbox CR Types:**\n- **Sandbox** (`agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`) -- Standard sandbox pod\n- **SandboxClaim** (`extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`) -- Warm pool claim (CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize > 0)\n\n**Lifecycle Annotations/Labels:**\n- `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id` -- Session tracking\n- `runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name` -- Template reference\n- `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name` -- Sandbox identifier\n- `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout` -- Idle timeout duration (e.g., \"15m\")\n- `last-activity-time` -- Read by agentd for idle cleanup\n- `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` -- Pod name annotation from agent-sandbox controller\n\n**Sandbox CR Spec Structure:**\n```yaml\nspec:\n  replicas: 1\n  lifecycle:\n    shutdownTime: \"2026-04-10T15:00:00Z\"  # now + TTL (default 8h)\n  ports:\n    - name: web\n      port: 8080\n      protocol: HTTP\n  podTemplate:\n    # corev1.PodSpec embedded here\n```\n\n**Lifecycle Management Flow:**\n1. **Creation:** WorkloadManager creates Sandbox CR -> waits for running -> stores in Redis/Valkey\n2. **Activity tracking:** Router updates `last-activity-time` annotation\n3. **Idle cleanup:** Agentd reconciler checks `last-activity-time + 15m`, deletes if expired\n4. **TTL cleanup:** Sandbox has `shutdownTime` in spec.lifecycle\n5. **GC:** Background goroutine (15s tick) lists expired/inactive from Store, deletes CR + Store entry\n6. **Manual deletion:** DELETE endpoint removes CR (idempotent) then Store entry\n\n---\n\n### 4. Task/Checklist Structure Pattern\n\n**Location:** `changes/AR-XXX/tasks.md`\n\n**Standard Format:**\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX 任务清单\n\n> **Stage**: ST-X (Stage name)\n> **Module**: `pkg/xxx`\n> **Language**: Go\n> **Size**: S/M/L\n\n---\n\n## T-001: Task Title\n\n- [ ] T-001.01 Subtask description\n- [ ] T-001.02 Subtask description\n\n**验收**: Acceptance criteria\n```\n\n**Key Characteristics:**\n- Tasks are numbered hierarchically: `T-001`, `T-001.01`, `T-001.02`, etc.\n- Each task has explicit **验收** (acceptance criteria)\n- Tasks progress from infrastructure -> implementation -> tests -> integration -> gate\n- Final task is always a \"全量验证门禁\" (full verification gate)\n- Stage indicators: ST-1 (Proposal), ST-3 (Design Complete), ST-4 (Implementation)\n\n**Existing Task Files:**\n\n| File | Stage | Module | Size | Status |\n|------|-------|--------|------|--------|\n| `changes/AR-001/tasks.md` | ST-4 | `pkg/apis` | S | Detailed (14 tasks, ~199 lines) |\n| `changes/AR-002/tasks.md` | ST-3 | `pkg/apis` | S | Detailed (15 tasks, ~180 lines) |\n| `changes/AR-003/tasks.md` | ST-1 | `pkg/apis` | S | Detailed (5 tasks, ~61 lines) |\n| `changes/AR-004/tasks.md` | ST-3 | `pkg/workloadmanager` | M | Detailed (17 tasks, ~255 lines) |\n| `changes/AR-005/tasks.md` | ST-3 | `pkg/workloadmanager` | M | Detailed (24 tasks, ~366 lines) |\n| `changes/AR-006/tasks.md` | -- | `pkg/workloadmanager` | M | **Stub only** (placeholder tasks, ~16 lines) |\n\n---\n\n### 5. Stage ST-3 Completion Artifacts and Design Documents\n\n**ST-3 = \"Design Complete\"**\n\nThree ARs are marked as ST-3:\n\n| AR | Title | Design Doc Status | Tasks Status |\n|----|-------|-------------------|--------------|\n| **AR-002** | CodeInterpreter CRD type definition | Design embedded in AR-001/design.md and sandbox-orchestration/design.md | Tasks fully detailed |\n| **AR-004** | WorkloadManager HTTP service framework | **Complete** (636 lines) -- `changes/AR-004/design.md` | Tasks fully detailed (17 tasks) |\n| **AR-005** | Sandbox creation handler | **Stub** (29 lines, all TODO) -- `changes/AR-005/design.md` | Tasks fully detailed (24 tasks) |\n\n**Key Design Documents:**\n\n| Document | Path | Description |\n|----------|------|-------------|\n| Main design | `design.md` | AR-003: Shared types extraction |\n| AR-001 design | `changes/AR-001/design.md` | AgentRuntime CRD (636 lines, comprehensive) |\n| AR-003 design | `changes/AR-003/design.md` | Shared types (155 lines) |\n| AR-004 design | `changes/AR-004/design.md` | HTTP service framework (636 lines, comprehensive) |\n| AR-005 design | `changes/AR-005/design.md` | Sandbox creation (STUB -- all TODO) |\n| AR-006 design | `changes/AR-006/design.md` | Sandbox deletion + GC (481 lines, comprehensive) |\n| Sandbox orchestration | `sandbox-orchestration/design.md` | System-wide design (475 lines) |\n| Sandbox orchestration spec | `sandbox-orchestration/spec.md` | BDD-style requirements (176 lines) |\n| Session store | `session-store/design.md` | Redis/Valkey store design (206 lines) |\n| Idle cleanup | `idle-cleanup/design.md` | Agentd reconciler design (126 lines) |\n| Delta spec | `delta-spec.md` | AR-004 BDD requirements (227 lines) |\n| client-go reference | `.sdd_prompt.md` | Generated client API reference (256 lines) |\n\n**AR-006 (Sandbox Deletion + Lifecycle) is the most relevant for future work:**\n- Defines `SandboxDeleteHandler` with DELETE endpoints\n- Defines `garbageCollector` (15s tick, 2min timeout, batch size 16)\n- Defines graceful shutdown sequence: HTTP -> GC -> Store.Close()\n- Includes detailed test case tables (14 delete tests + 9 GC tests)\n- Has alternatives analysis (finalizers, sync order, watch vs poll)\n\n---\n\n### 6. Testing Patterns\n\n**Test Framework:** `testing` package with `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert`\n\n**Test File Locations (6 existing test files):**\n\n| Test File | Path |\n|-----------|------|\n| `response_test.go` | `pkg/workloadmanager/response/response_test.go` |\n| `agent_type_test.go` | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type_test.go` |\n| `codeinterpreter_types_test.go` | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types_test.go` |\n| `constants_test.go` | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/constants_test.go` |\n| `shared_types_test.go` | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types_test.go` |\n| `groupversion_info_test.go` | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info_test.go` |\n\n**Testing Patterns Used:**\n\n1. **Gin test context pattern:**\n   ```go\n   gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)\n   w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n   c, _ := gin.CreateTestContext(w)\n   ```\n\n2. **Table-driven tests** (implied by task lists in AR-004/AR-005)\n\n3. **Fake Kubernetes clients:**\n   - `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake` for typed clientset\n   - `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake` for dynamic client\n   - Mock interfaces via `testify/mock`\n\n4. **TDD Manifest Requirements** (`testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md`):\n   - **T/C Ratio > 0.4** (test lines / code lines)\n   - Every source file must have a corresponding `*_test.go` file\n   - Core tests defined: Test-WM-1 through Test-WM-4, Test-RT-1 through Test-RT-4, Test-ST-1 through Test-ST-2, etc.\n\n5. **Coverage target:** >= 80% line coverage\n\n6. **Test execution:** `go test ./pkg/... -v -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n\n**Planned Test Files (from AR-005/AR-006 task lists):**\n- `handler/sandbox_create_test.go`\n- `handler/sandbox_model_test.go`\n- `handler/pod_ip_resolver_test.go`\n- `handler/sandbox_create_agent_runtime_test.go`\n- `handler/sandbox_create_code_interpreter_test.go`\n- `handler/sandbox_delete_test.go`\n- `handler/garbage_collector_test.go`\n- `config_test.go`\n- `server_test.go`\n- `routes_test.go`\n- `handler/health_test.go`\n- `handler/agent_runtime_test.go`\n- `handler/code_interpreter_test.go`\n- `middleware/request_id_test.go`\n\n---\n\n### 7. Related Modules and Dependencies\n\n**Direct Dependencies of `pkg/workloadmanager`:**\n\n| Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n|------------|--------|---------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Local | CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, TargetPort, etc.) |\n| `client-go/` | Local (generated) | Typed clients, informers, listers for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | External | HTTP framework |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | External | UUID v4 generation for session IDs |\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | External | PodSpec, Container, EnvVar types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | External | metav1, schema, unstructured, labels, errors |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | External | dynamic.Interface, kubernetes.Clientset, informers |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | External | ctrl.Manager, reconciler pattern |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` | External | Sandbox CRD types (sandboxv1alpha1) |\n\n**Consumers of `pkg/workloadmanager`:**\n\n| Consumer | Relationship |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Binary entry point (planned) |\n| `session-routing` (Router) | Calls WorkloadManager HTTP API to create/delete sandboxes |\n| `cli-toolkit` | Calls WorkloadManager HTTP API |\n| `python-sdk` | Calls WorkloadManager HTTP API |\n| `pkg/store` | Store interface used by workloadmanager for session persistence |\n| `pkg/agentd` | Reads `LastActivityAnnotationKey` constant from workloadmanager |\n\n**Store Interface (from `session-store/design.md`):**\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n**Key Configuration (from `sandbox-orchestration/design.md`):**\n- CLI flags: `-port` (8080), `-runtime-class-name` (kuasar-vmm), `-enable-tls`, `-tls-cert`, `-tls-key`, `-enable-auth`\n- Token cache: LRU, capacity 1000, TTL 5 minutes\n- GC interval: 15 seconds, tick timeout 2 minutes, batch limit 16\n- HTTP server: h2c wrapping, ReadTimeout 15s, IdleTimeout 90s\n- Graceful shutdown: HTTP 15s -> cancel GC ctx -> WaitForBackgroundWorkers -> CloseStore\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_288f641ffffeIXnIDAhsR5Db0L","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775818620414,"end":1775818838173}}}}
